node.title: Ukraine says financial and defense sites under attack by hackers
node.description: Ukrainian officials say some of their national security and financial sites are now under attack by hackers.

node.title: Freightways to build $40m cold store facility in Hamilton
node.description: National freight carrier Freightways is building a large, $40-million cold store facility in Hamilton to meet growing demand for fresh and frozen delivery services.

node.title: 'Time is fast running out': Protesters given ultimatum as police move to clear roads
node.description: Police is putting into action its Major Operations Centre at the headquarters in Wellington in a bid to quell protesters "unreasonably impacting the city".

node.title: Kerr sisters seal White Ferns win over India
node.description: The White Ferns have survived a close run chase against India to win the second ODI by three wickets.

node.title: Levi's president says she quit over pressure on COVID views

node.title: Surgeon general reflects on young daughter's COVID-19 experience
node.description: "In these moments, it doesn't matter if you're a doctor or Surgeon General. We are parents first," U.S. Surgeon General Vivek Murthy wrote.

node.title: Kamila Valieva leads women's short program after doping ruling
node.description: Valieva broke into tears after she dazzled with a slew of lutzes and spins, scoring 82.16 and putting her at the top of the women's figure skating leaderboard.

node.title: Wholesale prices jump, adding to inflation woes for consumers
node.description: The cost of producing food, energy and many other goods has surged nearly 10% from a year ago, new data shows.

node.title: More vouchers released for Auckland activities
node.description: Another 50,000 vouchers are being handed out for people to visit tourist attractions and council facilities in Auckland.

node.title: AI company raises $105m to create people for 'digital' workforces
node.description: An Auckland based artificial intelligence company Soul Machines has raised $US70 million ($NZ105m) to meet growing demand for "digital people".

node.title: Sandy Hook families settle for $73 million with gunmaker Remington
node.description: The families of nine victims have agreed to a $73 million settlement of a lawsuit against the maker of the rifle used to kill 20 first graders and six educators in 2012.

node.title: Prince Andrew settles sex abuse lawsuit with Virginia Giuffre
node.description: The suit was settled out of court and will require Andrew to donate to Guiffre's charity.

node.title: Simone Biles is engaged to Jonathan Owens
node.description: Simone Biles revealed she "woke up a fianceé," sharing photos of Owens' proposal.

node.title: Fishing boat sinks off Canada; 4 crew members dead, 15 missing
node.description: Two lifeboats were "completely empty," while in another, three survivors were found "in a state of hypothermic shock," officials said.

node.title: Cycling NZ find replacement sprint coach
node.description: Cycling New Zealand is rebuilding its high performance coaching group following the sudden departure of staff last year.

node.title: Stocks up after Russia pulls back some troops on Ukraine border
node.description: But Wall Street analysts caution that the potential for military conflict in the region remains high.

node.title: Judge speeds up review of lawyer's emails sought by January 6 committee

node.title: NYC fires 1,000-plus workers over vaccine mandate
node.description: Workers who refuse to comply with city's vaccine rule make up less than 1% of the city's workforce.

node.title: Rare Texas plant vital to bees and butterflies could be endangered

node.title: "Cautious optimism," but confusion over Russia's intentions in Ukraine

node.title: Snake on plane forces jet to divert

node.title: 42% of West megadrought linked to human-caused climate change

node.title: Winning $183 million Powerball ticket sold
node.description: The odds of winning the jackpot are 1 in 292.2 million.

node.title: Standoff as U.S. seeks extradition of Honduras' ex-president

node.title: Debris on track to hit the moon may not be SpaceX rocket after all

node.title: Maryland storing bodies in garage due to backup in coroner's office
node.description: The Baltimore garage and loading dock are being used to handle the overflow of remains awaiting autopsies. There's been a recent spike in deaths from COVID-17, overdoes and murders, a state legislator says.

node.title: Widow describes husband being shot in theater after argument over texting

node.title: Mummies of children unearthed in Peru. They were likely sacrificed.

node.title: Principal gets life sentence for raping at least 13 students

node.title: Russia says some troops pulling back from Ukraine border
node.description: Defense ministry says some of the troops and war machines massed for months along the border for "exercises" have "completed their tasks" and are heading back to base.
